		{
			"title" : "Santa Maria del Fiore",
			"elements" : [
				"The cathedral, started over two hundred and sixty years ago, was finished in the last century. It's almost ninety years now that the cross was placed over the dome that Brunelleschi designed. Now, it seems that Vasari (yes, the biographer of the artists and supreme gossiper, but a fine painter and architect himself) will be working on the frescoes as soon as he's done with the Uffizi. Too bad for the façade, though. It's still the plain stone of old times, and nobody really likes it—but nobody knows how to fix it."
			]
		},
