			"title" : "Santa Croce",
			"elements" : [
				"Santa Croce is the greatest Franciscan church in the world. It holds several chapels, some decorated by Giotto, and it's connected to the Franciscan convent. The refectory, which holds the Crucifix by Cimabue, is undergoing repairs after the 1557 flood. In the last two centuries the Franciscan have held the role of inquisitors in the city."
			]
		},
